you would then just rent
out a couple of rooms

259
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,530
and get them to pay off
your mortgage for you.

260
00:08:57,530 --> 00:08:58,363
Alternatively,

261
00:08:58,363 --> 00:09:00,050
if you don't want someone
to live in your house,

262
00:09:00,050 --> 00:09:01,350
you could buy a duplex,

263
00:09:01,350 --> 00:09:03,490
which is one house split into two

264
00:09:03,490 --> 00:09:05,050
with two separate entrances.

265
00:09:05,050 --> 00:09:06,950
If you don't like either
of these two options,

266
00:09:06,950 --> 00:09:09,800
then you could look into
becoming an Airbnb host.

267
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:11,810
The whole idea is to get other people

268
00:09:11,810 --> 00:09:13,340
to pay for your real estate

269
00:09:13,340 --> 00:09:14,610
so you don't have to.

270
00:09:14,610 --> 00:09:18,470
Number six is purchasing
cheap, reliable transportation.

271
00:09:18,470 --> 00:09:19,570
A used car is essential,

272
00:09:19,570 --> 00:09:22,280
as it will allow you to
work on your own schedule,

273
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:25,700
meet deadlines, and take advantage
of any new opportunities.

274
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:26,850
In my early twenties,

275
00:09:26,850 --> 00:09:29,230
I made the mistake of
having a really nice car.

276
00:09:29,230 --> 00:09:31,040
It was a Ford RS Turbo.

277
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:33,010
To be honest, I just wanted to show off

278
00:09:33,010 --> 00:09:34,950
to all my friends and
maybe get a girlfriend.

279
00:09:34,950 --> 00:09:37,760
Being a ginger back in the
eighties wasn't a great look,

280
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:39,830
I needed all the help I could get.

281
00:09:39,830 --> 00:09:41,540
that car ended up getting stolen

282
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:43,190
but it actually turned out great,

283
00:09:43,190 --> 00:09:45,230
cause I managed to get
an insurance payout.

284
00:09:45,230 --> 00:09:47,240
This time, instead of getting a new car,

285
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:49,980
I used the money to buy
cheap, used Peugeot.

286
00:09:49,980 --> 00:09:51,350
It wasn't much to look at,

287
00:09:51,350 --> 00:09:52,610
but I was in my twenties

288
00:09:52,610 --> 00:09:54,930
and no one expected me
to be a millionaire.

289
00:09:54,930 --> 00:09:56,490
So I used the rest of the money

290
00:09:56,490 --> 00:09:58,590
to invest and expand my business.

291
00:09:58,590 --> 00:10:00,300
I'd already met my future wife,

292
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:02,120
so I didn't need to impress anyone else.

293
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:04,480
The real lesson here is
that an expensive new car

294
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:05,770
does three things.

295
00:10:05,770 --> 00:10:07,210
It locks your money away,

296
00:10:07,210 --> 00:10:09,730
It could put you into debt
if you buy it on finance

297
00:10:09,730 --> 00:10:12,090
and it will lose value like crazy!

298
00:10:12,090 --> 00:10:15,540
Freeing up my cash helped expand
my business to new heights

299
00:10:15,540 --> 00:10:18,470
and of course, I had no fear
of the Peugeot getting stolen.

300
00:10:18,470 --> 00:10:19,303
To be honest,

301
00:10:19,303 --> 00:10:22,020
I don't think anyone's
ever stolen a beige car.

302
00:10:22,020 --> 00:10:24,680
The one exception for buying
a new car in your twenties

303
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:26,960
is if you think it's a
good financial decision

304
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:27,900
for your business.

305
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:30,850
This is the only reason
my 23 year old son Kurt

306
00:10:30,850 --> 00:10:32,590
has bought his Tesla Model three,

307
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:34,560
as he can write-off the entire car

308
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:37,240
as a business expense and get a tax break.

309
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,980
Before that he was driving around

310
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:41,480
a used 20 year old Toyota Yaris.

311
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:43,930
I always advised him
to live like a student

312
00:10:43,930 --> 00:10:47,010
for as long as possible and
invest as much as he could.

313
00:10:47,010 --> 00:10:48,210
I was happy to advise him,

314
00:10:48,210 --> 00:10:50,060
but I wasn't giving him any handouts.

315
00:10:50,060 --> 00:10:52,470
Number seven is buying Bitcoin.

316
00:10:52,470 --> 00:10:54,060
Bitcoin closed out 2020

317
00:10:54,060 --> 00:10:56,740
as the best performing
asset of the last decade.

318
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:59,530
So at this stage, it seems
silly not to own a little bit.

319
00:10:59,530 --> 00:11:00,930
I would love to share a story

320
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:02,650
of how Bitcoin changed my life,

321
00:11:02,650 --> 00:11:04,990
but it just wasn't around
back when I was younger.

322
00:11:04,990 --> 00:11:08,543
And you certainly couldn't
get up to $250 of free Bitcoin

323
00:11:08,543 --> 00:11:11,530
with the BlockFi link down
below when I was growing up!

324
00:11:11,530 --> 00:11:13,650
I'm all for diversifying my portfolio

325
00:11:13,650 --> 00:11:16,090
into crypto like Bitcoin and Ethereum

326
00:11:16,090 --> 00:11:18,860
As the growth has been insane
over the last two years,

327
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:21,330
and I'm excited to see
what the future holds.

328
00:11:21,330 --> 00:11:24,680
In my opinion, owning a small
percentage of wealth in crypto

329
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:25,730
is a good idea,

330
00:11:25,730 --> 00:11:27,790
but I do have a problem
with people YOLOing

331
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:29,610
their life savings into one asset

332
00:11:29,610 --> 00:11:32,740
in hopes that they can achieve
thousand percent returns.

333
00:11:32,740 --> 00:11:35,080
Take the Doge Coin
millionaire for example,

334
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:37,110
he invested around a quarter of a million

335
00:11:37,110 --> 00:11:40,070
into doge coin at 4.50 cents a coin,

336
00:11:40,070 --> 00:11:42,320
before the mainstream media and Elon Musk

337
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,440
tuck their claws in.

338
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:46,460
Among all the Elon madness
and mainstream media hype,

339
00:11:46,460 --> 00:11:48,790
he managed to rack up over 2 million

340
00:11:48,790 --> 00:11:50,290
from his Doge investment.

341
00:11:50,290 --> 00:11:51,940
fast forward it a few months,

342
00:11:51,940 --> 00:11:53,720
and he isn't even a millionaire anymore.

343
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:54,920
Now I'm sure he'll be okay,

344
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:56,820
and he's achieved huge returns,

345
00:11:56,820 --> 00:11:58,500
wherever he's a millionaire or not.

346
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,400
But the point I'm making is you never know

347
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:03,080
when all time highs and lows will be.

348
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:06,070
Crypto has undeniably
been returning investors

349
00:12:06,070 --> 00:12:08,080
more profit than the stock market,

350
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:11,050
so it makes perfect sense
to buy and hold some crypto,

351
00:12:11,050 --> 00:12:12,950
especially Bitcoin and Ethereum.

352
00:12:12,950 --> 00:12:15,560
Just remember to only
invest what you can to lose

353
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:17,750
and ensure your investment portfolio

354
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:21,070
is diversified across as
many sectors as possible.

355
00:12:21,070 --> 00:12:24,020
Here's a bonus one for everyone
who smashed the like button.

356
00:12:24,020 --> 00:12:25,200
If you haven't done that already,

357
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,630
you're gonna have to cover your ears.

358
00:12:26,630 --> 00:12:28,610
It's very important to
invest in your health,

359
00:12:28,610 --> 00:12:29,910
as the healthier you are,

360
00:12:29,910 --> 00:12:31,130
the harder you'll be able to work

361
00:12:31,130 --> 00:12:32,223
without becoming burnt-out.

362
00:12:32,223 --> 00:12:34,370
This is something I
learned a little bit later

363
00:12:34,370 --> 00:12:36,250
after becoming very ill in my twenties

364
00:12:36,250 --> 00:12:37,690
from grinding all the time.

365
00:12:37,690 --> 00:12:40,360
My doctor even told me I
needed to take a break!

366
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,640
So the big takeaway here

367
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:44,620
is your twenties are more
important than they might seem.

368
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:46,770
Compound interest is an amazing thing

369
00:12:46,770 --> 00:12:49,690
which can either set you up
for a lifetime of success

370
00:12:49,690 --> 00:12:52,250
or start you down a path
of snowballing debt.

371
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:54,120
As I mentioned before, in your twenties

372
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:56,080
you can afford to take
a little bit more risk

373
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:58,720
when it comes to investing
and starting a business.

374
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:00,380
This is because you have so much time

375
00:13:00,380 --> 00:13:02,500
to make your money back
if something goes wrong.

376
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:05,890
However, I still believe these
risks should be calculated

377
00:13:05,890 --> 00:13:07,720
and with a long-term plan in mind.

378
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,900
The people that look for
a way to get rich quick

379
00:13:09,900 --> 00:13:11,840
usually just end up being scammed

380
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:14,920
and then overtaken by the
people with a long-term outlook.

381
00:13:14,920 --> 00:13:16,560
A way to make this all easier for you

382
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:19,210
is to spend time with
people that are like-minded

383
00:13:19,210 --> 00:13:20,770
and more successful.

384
00:13:20,770 --> 00:13:24,320
this way, you won't be constantly
tempted into bad choices.

385
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,620
I always thought that buying things

386
00:13:25,620 --> 00:13:28,160
just to impress others
was a pointless pursuit

387
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:30,930
that would just leave me with
less money and less freedom.

388
